    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p>\u00a0</p>\n<p>\nAnuj has <b>K</b> samples of <b>N</b> tree saplings of initial height <b>h[i]</b>(1 based indexing).<br>\nHe plants these <b>K</b> samples of <b>N</b> trees in a line to get <b>N*K</b> saplings.<br>\nEg. <b>N=3,K=3</b> and heights are <b>1,2,3</b>.<br>\nThe final sequence will be <b>1,2,3,1,2,3,1,2,3</b>.\n<br><br>\nNow at the end of <b>i'th</b> year, he waters the trees from index <b>1</b> to index <b>i</b>, after which height of each tree is multiplied by <b>X</b>.\n<b>i</b> starts from <b>1</b> and goes till <b>N*K</b>.<br>\nAnuj wants to find the sum of heights of all trees at the end of <b>K*N'th</b> year modulo 10^9+7.\n<br><br>\nSince he cannot handle such large additions, he wants you to do it for him.\n(and find Harshit's 5T if possible)\n</p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n\n\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<p>\nFirst line contains the number of test cases, <b>T</b>\n<br>\nFirst line of each test case contains 3 space seperated integers <b>N</b>,<b>K</b> and <b>X</b>.\n<br>\nSecond line of each test case consists of <b>N</b> space seperated integers denoting the height of the trees.\n</p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<p>Print a single integer denoting the sum of height of all trees after the <b>K*N'th</b> year</p>\n\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<p>\n1<=<b>T</b><=100<br>\n1<=<b>N</b><=10^5<br>\n1<=<b>K,X,h[i]</b><=10^9\n</p>\n\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre><b>Input:</b>\n1\n3 2 2\n1 2 3\n\n<b>Output:</b>\n198\n</pre>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Explanation</h3>\n<p>\n<b>K*N</b> is 6.\nAt the end of first year, he waters the first tree. So its height is 2.\nAt the end of second year, he waters the first 2 trees so the new heights are 4,4.\nAt the end of third year, he waters the first 3 trees so the new heights are 8,8,6.\nAt the end of fourth year, he waters the first 4 trees so the new heights are 16,16,12,2.\nAt the end of fifth year, he waters the first 5 trees so the new heights are 32,32,24,4,4.\nAt the end of sixth year, he waters all the first 6 trees so the new heights are 64,64,48,8,8,6.\nSum of all the trees at the end of 6th year is 198.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n</p>",
